<div id="calendar-modal" class="modal fade" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="calendar-modal-title">
  <div class="modal-dialog">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h4 class="modal-title" id="calendar-modal-title">📆 Free Calendar Subscription</h4>
        <button type="button" class="close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">&times;</button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        <h5>For Mobile and Desktop</h5>
        <p>Automatically updating calendar for apps like Outlook, iOS &amp; macOS Calendar</p>
        <a class="ifsc-action-button ifsc-action-button-secondary" href="webcal://calendar.ifsc.stream" role="button" rel="noopener">Add to Device's Calendar</a>
        <hr />

        <h5>For Google Calendar</h5>
        <p>Automatically updating calendar for Google</p>
        <a class="ifsc-action-button ifsc-action-button-secondary" href="https://www.google.com/calendar/render?cid=webcal://calendar.ifsc.stream" target="_blank" rel="noopener" role="button">Add to Google Calendar</a>
        <hr />

        <h5>Download <code>.ics</code> file</h5>
        <p>Non-updating calendar (<code>.ics</code>) for calendars that can’t handle updating subscriptions</p>
        <a class="ifsc-action-button ifsc-action-button-secondary" href="https://calendar.ifsc.stream" target="_blank" rel="noopener" role="button">Download .ics</a>
        <a class="ifsc-action-button ifsc-action-button-secondary" href="https://github.com/sportclimbing/ifsc-calendar/wiki" role="button" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View Tutorial</a>
        <hr />

        <p class="small">This calendar will auto-update and be ready for future seasons as well. And it's fully <a href="https://github.com/sportclimbing">open source</a>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-footer">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

